JOHANNESBURG - A picture commemoration of South Africa's jazz heavyweight, Hugh Masekela. Masekela had been battling prostate cancer since his initial diagnosis in 2008. On Tuesday, he passed whilst surrounded by his loved ones. Hugh Masekela performs at the 16th Cape Town Cape Town International Jazz Festival. Photo: Denvor De Wee / Gallo Images South African legend musician Hugh Masekela during the annual MTN Bushfire Festival in Swaziland in 2017. Photo: Alet Pretorius / Gallo Images Hugh Masekela is a world-renowned flugelhorn player, trumpeter, bandleader, composer, and singer during the DStv Mzansi Viewers Choice Awards. Photo: Gallo Images / Frennie Shivambu Hugh Masekela performing at the Oppikoppi Festival in 2014. Photo: Gallo Images / John Hogg Hugh Masekela performing at the Joy of Jazz. Photo: Peter Eland / Gallo Images Hugh Masekela during one of his last performances at the DSTV Choice Awards. Photo: Gallo Images / Frennie Shivambu Hugh Masekela has died at the age of 78, following a long battle with prostate cancer. Photo: Bongiwe Gumede / Gallo Images eNCA